@node Creating a New Toot, , Managing Toots, Managing Toots
@section Creating a New Toot

Toot characters start off with a name and an appearance. We'll also give you
a few items with which to start your exploration.

Toot names are just like human names, but they all have to be unique. You
can join together word-parts with hyphens. Here are some Toot names:

@itemize
@item
Flora
@item
Null-Pointer-Exception
@item
Codfish-Howie
@end itemize

If you really want to include a number, it has to be the last part of a
name. You can't name a Toot something like ``99luftballoons,'' but you could
name them ``Luftballoons-99'' or so.

Toot characters have some basic  appearance settings, as well. You can
choose the base  color of your Toot's  skin, the color of  the pads of
their feet  and trunk,  and the  color of the  pattern on  their skin.
You can also choose what pattern they will have.

Once you've made  these choices, you can immediately  start playing as
your Toot character.

@node Toots for Children, , Creating a New Toot, Managing Toots
@section Toots for Children

You can also create a Toot character for a child (under the age of
13). A child account is special because they won't be able to play in
Tootsville without your permission.

WRITEME

@node Sensitive Players,  , Toots for Children, Managing Toots
@section Sensitive Players

We  all know  in the  real world  that certain  topics of  conversation
aren't appropriate to have around children; this is often summed up by
saying, ``don't talk about sex, religion, or politics.''

In  Tootsville, players  who  are  children or  who  have checked  the
``sensitive  player'' box  on their  login screen  are presented  with
a black diamond next to their name.

When  a sensitive  player (who  may  be a  child) is  nearby, a  black
diamond  will also  appear in  your chat  bar, to  remind you  to mind
your language.

If you decide you want to discuss adult topics, there are several bars
in Tootsville  in which children  are not  allowed, and where  you can
speak candidly about  any topic within reason. Of  course, hate speech
will never be tolerated.

